'''''Master of Magic''''' is a [[role-playing video game]] for the [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]] [[home computer]]s. It was distributed by [[Mastertronic]] in 1985 under its [[Mastertronic Added Dimension|M.A.D.]] label.

==Description==
The player controls an unnamed hero who has been dragged into a strange world by Thelric the Master of Magic while exploring caverns. Thelric is looking for an [[amulet]] which will provide him with [[immortality]] and, having taught the hero a few [[Magic (gaming)|spells]], sets him on a [[quest]] to find this artifact.

==Music==
The music for the Commodore 64 version was written by [[Rob Hubbard]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/zzap64-magazine-012/page/n105/mode/1up?view=theater|title = ZZap!64 Magazine Issue 012|date = April 1986}}</ref> and is an arrangement of the track ''Shibolet'' by ''[[Larry Fast|Synergy]]'' (on the album ''Audion'').

==Reception==
''Zzap!64'' were impressed by the game, awarding it a score of 88%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/zzap64-magazine-012/page/n105/mode/1up?view=theater|title = ZZap!64 Magazine Issue 012|date = April 1986}}</ref> ''[[Your Sinclair]]'''s review of the Spectrum version said that it was "a lot of fun to play".<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Hughes|first=Gwyn|date=2007|title=Master Of Magic|url=http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/articles/masterofmagic.htm|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305033030/http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/articles/masterofmagic.htm|archive-date=2016-03-05|access-date=2021-08-04|work=Your Sinclair}}</ref>

The game also received reviews in contemporary gaming magazines, such as ''[[Sinclair User]]'', ''[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]'', ''[[ZB (computing)|ZX Computing]]'', ''[[Computer Gamer]]'' and ''[[MicroHobby]]''.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-03-03|title=Master of Magic - World of Spectrum|url=http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0003054|access-date=2021-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303194116/http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0003054|archive-date=2016-03-03}}</ref>

